# Changelog

Human/AI-authored log of logical changes. Newest at the bottom. See CLAUDE.md §0
for the required entry format.

## 2026-07-04 — Secure R2 page bytes via IdP-gated presigned URLs
- What:
  - Added `PresignGet` to the R2 store and `ObjectStore` port; page URLs are now
    short-lived SigV4 presigned links (direct client→R2, no proxy hop).
  - Added `manga.read` scope + `MiddlewareScope`; gated `/v1/chapters/:id/pages`
    and the retired `/v1/image` proxy behind it. Catalog reads stay public.
  - Seeded a public `mihon-ios` PKCE client (Authorization Code + PKCE, no secret);
    admin client also granted `manga.read`. New `PRESIGN_TTL_SEC` + `IOS_REDIRECT_URIS` env.
- Why: make R2 bytes reachable only through an IdP-authenticated flow without
  routing bytes through the Go container (plan: bagaimana-mengamankan-r2-untuk-groovy-quokka).
- Files: internal/repository/r2/store.go, internal/service/{ports.go,manga_service.go},
  internal/oidc/{util.go,provider.go,middleware.go,seed.go,storage.go},
  internal/server/router.go, internal/config/config.go, internal/app/module.go,
  internal/handler/manga_handler.go, .env.example, wrangler.jsonc, worker/index.ts,
  regenerated mocks + swagger.
- Tests: updated internal/service/manga_service_test.go (presign fallback + error);
  `go build ./... && go vet ./... && go test ./...` → 107 pass.

